issue.title: [Feature Request]: add an option to highres.fix to save or stop after first pass
issue.body:
### Is there an existing issue for this?

- [X] I have searched the existing issues and checked the recent builds/commits

### What would your feature do ?

Enabling highres.fix for large images is a great feature, but sometimes when it gets at 50% (or first pass) the image is better (subjectively speaking) than the final image. 

The idea would be to add a new checkbox inside the "Highres.fix" option, or in the settings tab. Either to save after first pass, or to just do a single pass.

### Proposed workflow

1. Enable "Highres.fix"
2. Set with, height and denoise streng
3. Check a new box called "single pass" (or save first pass)
4. and then click "Generate" 


### Additional information

The option to save or stop is mentioned here as I don't know what is best for development, Either way, having an image just after the first pass would be great. Thanks!

issue.title: Split Generate/Interrupt button

labels.name: bug-report
labels.description: Report of a bug, yet to be confirmed

issue.body:
**Describe the bug**
When running from colab, some underlying connection seems very flaky, making it stop showing result images or be notified at all about the server process. That makes de Generate button unavailable and force you reload and rewrite all prompt, parameters img2img setup all over again.

**To Reproduce**
Steps to reproduce the behavior:
1. Go to https://colab.research.google.com/drive/1Iy-xW9t1-OQWhb0hNxueGij8phCyluOh
2. Click on Generate a couple of times (more often with batches greater than 3 o 4)
4. See that the images are generated in the output folder, but the Interrupt button is present and can't generate more images.

**Expected behavior**
Leave the Generate button still accessible, so even if you reach this error you can continue to generate more images.


**Desktop (please complete the following information):**
 - OS: COLAB
 - Browser: chrome
 - Commit revision maybe from aa1d1bf44ece3f0495873fc3129d2dba664f8c2f onwards. The connection issues looks like a Colab/Gradio thing, but that's the commit of the button integration.

**Additional context**
The lost connection issues looks like a Colab/gradio thing, it happens all the time, but I'm assuming that this is not an issue with your repo.

issue.title: DreamBooth Stable Diffusion training now possible in 12.5GB VRAM, and it runs about 2 times faster.
issue.body:
Hey, So I managed to run Stable Diffusion dreambooth training in just 17.7GB GPU usage by replacing the attention with memory efficient flash attention from [xformers](https://github.com/facebookresearch/xformers). Along with using way less memory, it also runs 2 times faster. So it's possible to train SD in 24GB GPUs now. Tested on Nvidia A10G, took 15-20 mins to train. I hope it's helpful.

Code in my fork: https://github.com/ShivamShrirao/diffusers/blob/main/examples/dreambooth/

![Screenshot_20220927_042425](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/37087513/192394776-17dde282-4e5a-48b5-8ed4-28ec3e98b985.png)

### Can even train on batch size of 2.

![Screenshot_20220927_042648](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/37087513/192395033-e364cb60-f569-4843-931b-72a6d9aa85e3.png)

With some more tweaks it might be possible to train even on 16 GB gpus.

And it works, Outputs: Me in Fortnite
![Me in Fortnite](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/37087513/192395417-f3651fcd-579c-44de-9efa-3fdc409caf51.jpg)

4. and then click "Generate" 


### Additional information

The option to save or stop is mentioned here as I don't know what is best for development, Either way, having an image just after the first pass would be great. Thanks!

issue.title: Split Generate/Interrupt button

labels.name: bug-report
labels.description: Report of a bug, yet to be confirmed

issue.body:
**Describe the bug**
When running from colab, some underlying connection seems very flaky, making it stop showing result images or be notified at all about the server process. That makes de Generate button unavailable and force you reload and rewrite all prompt, parameters img2img setup all over again.

**To Reproduce**
Steps to reproduce the behavior:
1. Go to https://colab.research.google.com/drive/1Iy-xW9t1-OQWhb0hNxueGij8phCyluOh
2. Click on Generate a couple of times (more often with batches greater than 3 o 4)
4. See that the images are generated in the output folder, but the Interrupt button is present and can't generate more images.

**Expected behavior**
Leave the Generate button still accessible, so even if you reach this error you can continue to generate more images.


**Desktop (please complete the following information):**
 - OS: COLAB
 - Browser: chrome
 - Commit revision maybe from aa1d1bf44ece3f0495873fc3129d2dba664f8c2f onwards. The connection issues looks like a Colab/Gradio thing, but that's the commit of the button integration.

**Additional context**
The lost connection issues looks like a Colab/gradio thing, it happens all the time, but I'm assuming that this is not an issue with your repo.

issue.title: DreamBooth Stable Diffusion training now possible in 12.5GB VRAM, and it runs about 2 times faster.
issue.body:
Hey, So I managed to run Stable Diffusion dreambooth training in just 17.7GB GPU usage by replacing the attention with memory efficient flash attention from [xformers](https://github.com/facebookresearch/xformers). Along with using way less memory, it also runs 2 times faster. So it's possible to train SD in 24GB GPUs now. Tested on Nvidia A10G, took 15-20 mins to train. I hope it's helpful.

Code in my fork: https://github.com/ShivamShrirao/diffusers/blob/main/examples/dreambooth/

![Screenshot_20220927_042425](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/37087513/192394776-17dde282-4e5a-48b5-8ed4-28ec3e98b985.png)

### Can even train on batch size of 2.

![Screenshot_20220927_042648](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/37087513/192395033-e364cb60-f569-4843-931b-72a6d9aa85e3.png)

With some more tweaks it might be possible to train even on 16 GB gpus.

And it works, Outputs: Me in Fortnite
![Me in Fortnite](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/37087513/192395417-f3651fcd-579c-44de-9efa-3fdc409caf51.jpg)

https://github.com/huggingface/diffusers/pull/554#issuecomment-1258751183
